<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2384&amp;p=18881#p18881"><![CDATA[
Like the NES, there is no BIOS (except for the 64-byte boot loader ROM used by the SPC-700).  So the info there will only get read if the game program accesses it.  But it does make life easier for any game copier devices.  So yeah, must've been for verification or something.  Can't imagine it'd be much more efficient than writing it on an attached piece of paper though, I mean how often would they be making new maskroms? heheh.<br /><br />Oh, one other bit of info in there I forgot to mention is that it specifies the ROM version too.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Fri Oct 27, 2006 12:01 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
