<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2384&amp;p=18874#p18874"><![CDATA[
Yeah, SNES ROMs have info at the end of the first bank that says the game name, maker, ROM size, checksum, banking type, SRAM size, extra chips, and I think that's about it.  When I made my NSF player I had to use ucon64 to fix the checksum (well, didn't <em>have</em> to obviously, but I wanted it correct).<br /><br />Also some games will check the PPU and not run if it's the wrong region.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Fri Oct 27, 2006 10:17 am</p><hr />
